{
    "name": "JSON:Presenter",
    "description": "A demo presentation that outlines the features of JSON:Presenter",
    "aspectW": 16,
    "aspectH": 9,
    "container": {
        "border": "1px solid black",
        "background": "black"
    },
    "defaults": {
        "fontFace": "Times New Roman,serif",
        "fontSize": 50,
        "fontWeight": "normal",
        "fontStyle": "normal",
        "fontColor": "white",
        "textAlign": "left",
        "blockLeft" : 0,
        "blockTop" : 0,
        "blockBackground" : "none",
        "blockBorder": "none",
        "blockPadding": "1em"
    },
    "blocks": {
        "title 1": {
            "type": "text",
            "spec": {
                "blockTop": 300,
                "blockWidth": 1000,
                "blockHeight": 300,
                "textAlign": "center",
                "fontFace": "Helvetica,sans-serif",
                "fontSize": 200,
                "fontWeight": "bold"
            }
        },
        "title 2": {
            "type": "text",
            "spec": {
                "blockWidth": 1000,
                "blockHeight": 150,
                "textAlign": "center",
                "fontFace": "Helvetica,sans-serif",
                "fontSize": 100,
                "fontWeight": "bold"
            }
        },
        "body": {
            "type": "text",
            "spec": {
                "blockTop": 200,
                "blockWidth": 1000,
                "blockHeight": 800
            }
        }
    },
    "content":  {
        "presenter title": "JSON:Presenter",
        "slide 1": [
            "JSON:Presenter&copy; lets you create PowerPoint-like presentations that can be run anywhere equipped with a suitable presentation engine; most notably in a web browser.",
            
            "Web-based presentations can run from any host, including static; all you need is one CDN-hosted JavaScript file and you're good to go.",
            
            "Rather than being created in a GUI, presentations are JSON text files having a format that can be implemented by any suitable engine.",
            
            "The first engine available is a component of the EasyCoder&trade; browser scripting language but it can be used completely independently of the latter."
        ]
    },
    "steps": [
        {
            "action": "show",
            "items": [
                {
                    "block": "title 1",
                    "content": "presenter title"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "action": "hold",
            "duration": 10
        },
        {
            "action": "hide",
            "items": [
                {
                    "block": "title 1",
                    "content": "presenter title"
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}
